'''Slithese''', or '''Slithian''', was the [[Language/Legends|language]] spoken by the [[Slith]] species of [[Yavin 13/Legends|Yavin 13]], the sounds of which were produced by rubbing their rough scales over the ground. A number of simple signals could be produced, which conveyed different meanings. The language could be learned by non-Slith also; a number of [[Gerb]] learned this skill as a self-defense mechanism. Since Slith lacked vocal cords, they were unable to speak [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]], and while they were able to produce some vocal noises, the unavoidable consequence of moisture evaporation discouraged this developing into an actual language.

